  partnership: [{ year: "2025", q: "The maximum number of partners in a professional firm, such as that of solicitors or accountants, is", options: ["A. five", "B. unlimited", "C. between ten and twenty", "D. between twenty and thirty"], answer: "B", exp: "Under Nigerian law (Companies and Allied Matters Act — CAMA) and general partnership law, the rules on maximum partners are:\n\n• Ordinary partnerships (non-professional): Previously capped at 20 partners under old law. Under CAMA 2020, this restriction has been relaxed.\n\n• Professional firms (solicitors, accountants, medical practitioners, etc.): The maximum number of partners is UNLIMITED. This exception exists because professional firms (like law firms and accounting firms) need to be able to grow and take on as many qualified partners as needed to serve clients effectively, and their professional regulatory bodies provide the necessary oversight and liability controls.\n\nThis is why large accounting firms (like PwC, Deloitte, KPMG) and law firms can have hundreds of partners worldwide — the unlimited exception applies precisely to professional service firms.\n\nSo for solicitors and accountants specifically, there is no cap on the number of partners. Answer: B — unlimited." },
                
    { year: "2025", q: "The following information was extracted from the books of a partnership. Net profit for the year is ₦120,000. Interest on capital is 5%. Interest on drawings is 10%. Profit sharing ratio is Adewumi 2/3 and Biodun 1/3. What is the profit to be shared by the partners for the year?", table: { headers: ["Particulars", "Adewumi (₦)", "Biodun (₦)"], rows: [["Capital Account", "160,000", "80,000"], ["Drawings Account", "40,000", "24,000"]] }, options: ["A. ₦104,000", "B. ₦114,400", "C. ₦116,000", "D. ₦120,000"], answer: "B", exp: "Step 1: Interest on Capital = (₦160,000 × 5%) + (₦80,000 × 5%) = ₦8,000 + ₦4,000 = ₦12,000. Step 2: Interest on Drawings = (₦40,000 × 10%) + (₦24,000 × 10%) = ₦4,000 + ₦2,400 = ₦6,400. Step 3: Shareable profit = Net profit - Interest on Capital + Interest on Drawings = ₦120,000 - ₦12,000 + ₦6,400 = ₦114,400." },
    { year: "2020", q: "The following information was extracted from the books of a partnership. Net profit for the year is ₦120,000. Interest on capital is 5%. Interest on drawings is 10%. Profit sharing ratio is Adewumi 2/3 and Biodun 1/3. Calculate Adewumi's share of profit.", table: { headers: ["Particulars", "Adewumi (₦)", "Biodun (₦)"], rows: [["Capital Account", "160,000", "80,000"], ["Drawings Account", "40,000", "24,000"]] }, options: ["A. ₦76,267", "B. ₦76,000", "C. ₦84,267", "D. ₦38,133"], answer: "A", exp: "Step 1: Shareable profit = ₦120,000 - (₦8,000 + ₦4,000) + (₦4,000 + ₦2,400) = ₦114,400. Step 2: Adewumi's share = ₦114,400 × 2/3 = ₦76,266.67 ≈ ₦76,267. Interest on capital is deducted from net profit, while interest on drawings is added back before sharing." },
    { year: "2025", q: "In the absence of a partnership deed,", options: ["A. partners remuneration is 5% of profit.", "B. no remuneration will be paid to a partner.", "C. remuneration will be paid equally to partners.", "D. remuneration will be paid to active partner."], answer: "B", exp: "Under the Partnership Act 1890 (still applicable in Nigeria), if no partnership deed exists, no partner is entitled to remuneration or salary for working in the business. All partners share profits equally, but no partner gets a fixed salary or commission." },
    { year: "2020", q: "If the partnership agreement does not specify how net profit is to be divided, the profit should be shared:", options: ["A. equally.", "B. in accordance with an established ratio.", "C. in proportion to the current account balance.", "D. in proportion to the weighted average of capital invested during the period."], answer: "A", exp: "Section 24 of the Partnership Act 1890 states that if no agreement exists, profits and losses are shared equally among partners, regardless of capital contributions. This default rule applies unless the partners have agreed otherwise in a deed." },
    { year: "2025", q: "The ability of a partner to enter into a contract on behalf of all partners is called:", options: ["A. mutual agency.", "B. partnership deed.", "C. partnership consent.", "D. partnership right."], answer: "A", exp: "Mutual agency is a key feature of a partnership where each partner acts as an agent of the firm. Any partner can bind the partnership and all other partners to contracts made in the ordinary course of business, unless third parties know of restrictions." },
    { year: "2020", q: "In Partnership, where there is no Partnership Agreement the business:", options: ["A. profits and losses are shared equally.", "B. salaries are paid to the general partner only.", "C. profit and losses are shared in a ratio.", "D. partners do not receive interest on their capital."], answer: "A", exp: "Under the Partnership Act 1890, if no partnership deed exists, profits and losses are shared equally. Also, no partner gets salary or interest on capital unless agreed. Option A is correct." },
  ],

